'Participation': {'def': 'A participation is the portion of an event which depends exclusively on a single object. Each of participations is itself an event that can be complex or atomic but which existentially depends on a single substantial. Take for instance the event e: the stabbing of Caesar by Brutus. In this event we have the participation of Caesar himself, of Brutus and of the knife. In this case, e is composed of the individual participation of each of these entities.', 'ref': 'UFO.html#UFO_Participation_detail'},
